is mature transcendental-philosophical analyses of reduction and constitution, to his late analyses of intersubjectivity and lifeworld. It can consequently serve as a concise and updated introduction to his thinking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362029240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503620292423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503620292/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles